name: UCO Bank
address:

6JGX+F36, Vivekanand Nagar, Janta Colony, Raipur, Chhattisgarh 492001

reviews.text:
A typical public sector bank. Customer preference always comes second after bank employee preference. I have had an account here since 2015. The services have improved in a major way since that time but it still lags in comparison to a private bank. The bank offers all the typical services of a public sector bank such as savings account, current account, various loans, etc. However, like almost every PSB, the process of availing those services is very lengthy and time consuming.
Few points -

Staff behaviour: The staff in 2015 was the most pathetic one I ever came across even when compared to that of SBI at that time. The deputy manager at that timewas so slow that I can figuratively compare him wiith a sloth and then too, the sloth would have won wrt the speed of doing work. However, the staff behaviour has substantially changed now-a-days and the gap has abridged compared to that of a private bank. After the staff completely changed in the branch after 2015, there had been two deputy managers since and both of them were at par in terms of dedication to their work and the quality of their work. They both complained about the immense amount of work pressure on them, but never compromised with their service quality. However, given the strict guidelines by the RBI, a strong private sector bank will always outweigh a public bank due to their focus on competitiveness and customer satisfaction. I therefore believe that if all other costs remain the same, why not choose a private bank?

Accessibility: It is situated near education department's office, although, reaching here is a little bit tricky if one doesn't use Google maps. However, it is very near to the Raipur ring road.

Not Disabled friendly: The office as well as the parking is not at all disabled friendly. There is no ramp available, plus the parking surface is uneven and doesn't have a separate parking space for the disabled.

Parking: Very small space in front of the bank is available for parking which is insufficient. Though the sidewalk tiles have been placed but the surface is uneven.

Additionally, the app of the bank is also very slow, unresponsive and it malfunctions many a times.

Overall, I would not recommend anyone to open an account in UCO bank if they have an option of any other bank.

reviews.text:
Dear everyone.
With a very sad note I need to inform you that I was promised a home loan @ 8.3% by Mr Mayur Uco bank Maninagar, Ahmedabad branch. The loan was sanctioned on 20 Nov 24 and first amount of 13680300/- was disbursed on 26 Nov( Last date of payment to builder was 27 Nov).
But to utter surprise he got it sanctioned for 8.35% without any prior information to me just a day prior to builder payment. I got stuck as I had no reaction time but to agree at that point in time . The meeting was in Adani realty office( builder) and Mr Ankit uco bank area manager also present.  The customer has no option but to accept.
Kindly note that just a day prior to last date of payment to the builder, he comes out with the sanction letter of 8.35% and that too EMI for total loan amount and not what was disbursed. This was again not disclosed by him in face-to-face during first meeting with me at my home regarding loan details along with one more UCO bank representative . He promised that it was only for the sanction and will finally it will be 8.3% only. This point was time and again clarified by me from him which he always justified. But he always kept me in dark till date.
What needs to be highlighted here is that this person lures the customers by false promises and puts them in a situation where there is no option I.e last date of payment of loan. This is ridiculous and he is a misfit in your organisation . He is supported by Mr Ankit, his superior , who works hand in hand by luring customers initially and later backing off.
Also, The EMI has been set at full loan amount but it is construction linked which was very well discussed with him. And he denies it now. I should pay EMI for the loan which has been disbursed and NOT for the total loan amount. This is illegal and I never approved it.
The date for EMI was discussed for 02nd
of each month which is again not finalised and the date has surpassed. Same issue was also discussed with Mr Ankit but he is Mr friend of Mayur . Even It was brought was very categorically by me on a call with him too stating these issues created by Mr Mayur which he had agreed to rectify but backing off now. This is absolutely stupidity and calls for legal action against them.
Nevertheless, Appropriate action for mental and financial harassment is being initiated by me against both legally and will be widely circulated on social media as well to warn other customers not to fall in their trap.
Dear team, kindly take suitable and immediate action against these two people who lure the customers towards lower ROI and other related promises. And keep things pending till the last date.
I have tried my level best to get to the correct conclusion as promised by them. Now even Mr Ankit is in denial mode. There has been no response, and they are not responding to the calls.  Kindly act pls ASAP.

Organisation Structure

Headquartered in Kolkata, the Bank has 42 Zonal Offices spread all over India. Branches located in a geographical area report to the Zonal Office having jurisdiction over that area. These Zonal Offices are headed by Senior Executives ranging upto the rank of Deputy General Manager, depending on size of business and importance of location. The Zonal Offices report to 8 Circle Offices headed by General Managers/senior Deputy General Managers.

Our Commitment to Customers

In all our promotional activities, we will be fair and reasonable in highlighting the salient features of the schemes marketed by us. Misleading or unfair highlighting of any aspect of any scheme/service marketed by the Bank leading to unfair practice shall not be resorted to by the Bank.

In commemorating the 50th Year of Independence of India, the Bank released a booklet entitled "Our Commitment to Customers" incorporating the Citizens’ Charter on services provided by the Bank.

In our continuing endeavour to serve our customers better, we have considerably extended the business hours for public transaction at the branches on all week-days.

reviews.text:
I had a very disappointing experience at this branch. I visited to inquire about opening a forex-related account, but the service was absolutely appalling. There was no manager available, and the assistant manager’s behavior was beyond rude, as if I had come to ask for something personal instead of professional assistance.

He didn’t even show the basic courtesy to ask me to sit or listen properly to my queries. When I inquired about another officer, I saw him sitting there doing nothing, completely indifferent to my request. I ended up waiting for 20 minutes with no resolution until I had to ask again.

Such unprofessional and disrespectful behavior is unacceptable. Banks are supposed to prioritize customer service, but this branch seems to have no regard for it. I won’t be returning, and I strongly advise others to avoid this place unless they improve their staff’s attitude and service standards.

reviews.text:
UCO Bank, formerly United Commercial Bank, established in 1943 in Kolkata, is a major government-owned commercial bank of India. During FY 2013-14, its total business was ₹4.55 lakh crore. Based on 2014 data, it is ranked 1860 on Forbes Global 2000 List. UCO Bank was ranked 294th among India's most trusted brands according to the Brand Trust Report 2014, a study conducted by Trust Research Advisory.It was a rise of 796 ranks considering it was listed at the 1090th position among India's most trusted brands in the Brand trust Report 2013.As of 30 March 2017 the bank had 4,000 plus service units 49 zonal offices spread all over India. It also has two overseas branches in Singapore and Hong Kong. UCO Bank's headquarters is on BTM Sarani, Kolkata.
As on 31 March 2012, government share-holding in the bank was 84%. Branch expansion started at a fast pace, particularly in rural areas, and the bank achieved several unique distinctions in Priority Sector lending and other social uplift activities. To keep pace with the developing scenario and expansion of business, the Bank undertook an exercise in organisational restructuring in the year 1972. This resulted in more functional specialisation, decentralisation of administration and emphasis on development of personnel skill and attitude. Side by side, whole hearted commitment into the government's poverty alleviation programmes continued and the convenorship of State Level Bankers' Committee (SLBC) was entrusted on the Bank for Odisha and Himachal Pradesh in 1983.total numbers of branch more than 4,000.
The logo of UCO bank consists of a pair of clasped hands covered with an octagonal structure. It has been coloured blue since the organisation's inception, blue representing the Bank's national responsibility. The background has remained yellow since the beginning as well.

reviews.text:
UCO Bank, formerly United Commercial Bank, established in 1943 in Kolkata, is a major government-owned commercial bank of India. During FY 2013-14, its total business was ₹ 4.55 lakh crore. Based on 2014 data, it is ranked 1860 on Forbes Global 2000 List. UCO Bank was ranked 294th among India's most trusted brands according to the Brand Trust Report 2014, a study conducted by Trust Research Advisory.[2] It was a rise of 796 ranks considering it was listed at the 1090th position among India's most trusted brands in the Brand trust Report 2013.[3] As of 30 March 2017 the bank had 4,000 plus service units 49 zonal offices spread all over India. It also has two overseas branches in Singapore and Hong Kong. UCO Bank's headquarters is on BTM Sarani, Kolkata.
Organisation Structure
Headquartered in Kolkata, the Bank has 42 Zonal Offices spread all over India. Branches located in a geographical area report to the Zonal Office having jurisdiction over that area. These Zonal Offices are headed by Senior Executives ranging upto the rank of Deputy General Manager, depending on size of business and importance of location. The Zonal Offices report to 8 Circle Offices headed by General Managers/senior Deputy General Managers.
Our Commitment to Customers
In all our promotional activities, we will be fair and reasonable in highlighting the salient features of the schemes marketed by us. Misleading or unfair highlighting of any aspect of any scheme/service marketed by the Bank leading to unfair practice shall not be resorted to by the Bank.
In commemorating the 50th Year of Independence of India, the Bank released a booklet entitled "Our Commitment to Customers" incorporating the Citizens’ Charter on services provided by the Bank.
In our continuing endeavour to serve our customers better, we have considerably extended the business hours for public transaction at the branches on all week-days.

recently visited the UCO Bank branch near Orbit Mall, Civil Lines, Jaipur, with my aunt to address a transaction issue. Unfortunately, our experience was extremely disappointing due to the unprofessional behavior of the staff.
The male staff were very rude and dismissive. When I asked for a solution to our issue, they replied harshly, stating, "We can’t do anything, and you’re not even our customer." Such a response is unacceptable in a service-oriented environment.

The branch manager, instead of addressing our concern, was busy on a phone call, during which he used abusive language in front of us. This behavior, especially in front of women, is highly inappropriate and unprofessional.

his experience left us feeling frustrated and disrespected. I would strongly advise others to think twice before opening an account at this branch. While UCO Bank is a government bank, the lack of accountability and basic courtesy from the staff is unacceptable.

I hope the bank takes steps to improve its customer service and ensure that such incidents do not happen in the future.
